## 2. RESCUE DOMAIN (from rescue.ts)

Source File: src/redux/ducks/rescue.ts (complete file, 102 lines)

Types to create in rescue.model.ts:
```typescript
export interface ResgateResponse {
  status: {
    message: string;
  };
  data?: {
    status: string;
  };
}

export interface RescuePayload {
  value: number;
  campaignId?: string;
  productCode?: string;
  description: string;
  participantId?: string;
}

export enum RescueStatus {
  IDLE = 'idle',
  LOADING = 'loading',
  SUCCESS = 'success',
  ERROR = 'error',
}

export interface RescueState {
  status: RescueStatus;
  responseStatus?: { message: string };
  error?: string;
}

export interface RescueActions {
  setStatus: (status: RescueStatus) => void;
  setResponseStatus: (responseStatus?: { message: string }) => void;
  setError: (error?: string) => void;
  reset: () => void;
}
```

Redux state being replaced:
  - isLoading: boolean (default: false)
  - isError: boolean (default: false)
  - status: ResgateResponse['status'] | undefined (default: undefined)

Redux actions being replaced:
  - rescueRequest(data) -> setStatus(LOADING) + call service with callbacks
  - rescueSuccess({ status }) -> setResponseStatus(status) + setStatus(SUCCESS)
  - rescueFailed({ status }) -> setResponseStatus(status) + setStatus(ERROR)
  - rescueClear() -> reset()

NOTE: rescueRequest accepts callbacks (onSuccess, onFailed) - handle in service/hook

