REDUX TO MIGRATE (3 Domains)
================================================================================

## 1. PRODUCTS DOMAIN (from points.ts)

Source File: src/redux/ducks/points.ts (lines 42-56, 86-88, 108-115, 149-165, 311-316)

Types to create in products.model.ts:
```typescript
export interface PointsProduct {
  name: string;
  redemptionOrigin?: string;
  convertionFactor?: number;
  minRedemptionValue?: number;
  productCode?: string;
  campaingId?: string;
  conversionFactor?: number;
  icon?: string;
  code?: string;
  origin?: string;
  points?: number;
  action?: string | null;
  campaignId?: string | null;
}

export enum PointsProductsStatus {
  IDLE = 'idle',
  LOADING = 'loading',
  SUCCESS = 'success',
  ERROR = 'error',
}

export interface PointsProductsState {
  products: PointsProduct[];
  status: PointsProductsStatus;
  error?: string;
}

export interface PointsProductsActions {
  setStatus: (status: PointsProductsStatus) => void;
  setProducts: (products: PointsProduct[]) => void;
  setError: (error?: string) => void;
  reset: () => void;
}
```

Redux state being replaced:
  - products: PointsProduct[] (default: [])
  - isLoadingProducts: boolean (default: true)
  - isErrorProducts: boolean (default: false)

Redux actions being replaced:
  - requestPointsProducts() -> setStatus(LOADING)
  - successPointsProducts(products) -> setProducts(products)
  - failedPointsProducts() -> setStatus(ERROR) + setError(msg)

Files to create:
  - src/services/api/products.api.ts (HTTP client)
  - src/services/models/products.model.ts (types above)
  - src/services/repository/products.repository.ts (data mapping)
  - src/services/services/products.service.ts (business logic)
  - src/services/store/products.store.ts (Zustand slice)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 2. RESCUE DOMAIN (from rescue.ts)

Source File: src/redux/ducks/rescue.ts (complete file, 102 lines)

Types to create in rescue.model.ts:
```typescript
export interface ResgateResponse {
  status: {
    message: string;
  };
  data?: {
    status: string;
  };
}

export interface RescuePayload {
  value: number;
  campaignId?: string;
  productCode?: string;
  description: string;
  participantId?: string;
}

export enum RescueStatus {
  IDLE = 'idle',
  LOADING = 'loading',
  SUCCESS = 'success',
  ERROR = 'error',
}

export interface RescueState {
  status: RescueStatus;
  responseStatus?: { message: string };
  error?: string;
}

export interface RescueActions {
  setStatus: (status: RescueStatus) => void;
  setResponseStatus: (responseStatus?: { message: string }) => void;
  setError: (error?: string) => void;
  reset: () => void;
}
```

Redux state being replaced:
  - isLoading: boolean (default: false)
  - isError: boolean (default: false)
  - status: ResgateResponse['status'] | undefined (default: undefined)

Redux actions being replaced:
  - rescueRequest(data) -> setStatus(LOADING) + call service with callbacks
  - rescueSuccess({ status }) -> setResponseStatus(status) + setStatus(SUCCESS)
  - rescueFailed({ status }) -> setResponseStatus(status) + setStatus(ERROR)
  - rescueClear() -> reset()

NOTE: rescueRequest accepts callbacks (onSuccess, onFailed) - handle in service/hook

Files to create:
  - src/services/api/rescue.api.ts
  - src/services/models/rescue.model.ts
  - src/services/services/rescue.service.ts
  - src/services/store/rescue.store.ts
  - src/services/hooks/useRescue.ts (for callback handling)

